.\" Manpage for gitcommit
.TH man 1 "04 May 2026" "202605041330-git" "gitcommit"

.SH NAME
gitcommit \- Self-contained Git repository commit management tool

.SH DESCRIPTION
A powerful, self-contained command-line tool for managing Git commits with intelligent file tracking, automated commit messages, changelog generation, and version management. Includes support for conventional commits, emoji commits, and custom commit workflows without any external dependencies.

.SH SYNOPSIS
gitcommit [options] [directory] [commands] [message]

.SH REPOSITORY MANAGEMENT COMMANDS
.TP
.B status, s
Show Git repository status
.TP
.B log [limit]
Show Git commit log (optionally limit number of results)
.TP
.B log show [commit]
Show full commit details including diff and stats. Without a commit hash, shows the most recent commit excluding patterns in GITCOMMIT_LOG_SHOW_EXCLUDE (default: excludes "Version Bump:")
.TP
.B log search <query>
Search through log for specific terms
.TP
.B search <query>
Search through commit history for specific terms
.TP
.B is clean|dirty
Check if repository is clean or dirty
.TP
.B init
Initialize a new Git repository
.TP
.B setup [all|org]
Initialize and configure a new Git repository. Use 'all' or 'org' to setup multiple repos in a directory.
.TP
.B reset
Reset the Git repository to clean state
.TP
.B branch
Create a new branch
.TP
.B pull
Pull changes from remote repository
.TP
.B push
Push committed changes to remote repository
.TP
.B merge <branch> [strategy] [message]
Smart merge with automatic strategy detection. Strategies: auto (default), ff (fast-forward only), no-ff (always merge commit), squash (squash all commits)
.TP
.B merge-resolve [action]
Resolve merge conflicts. Actions: status (default), show, edit, ours, theirs, abort
.TP
.B tag [add|remove|version] [args]
Manage Git tags. Subcommands: add <tag> <message>, remove <tag>, version <version> <message>
.TP
.B tar
Create a tar archive release
.TP
.B version
Bump version number and create version commit
.TP
.B fixup
Automatically amend last real commit with current changes, skipping Version Bump commits
.TP
.B squash [number] [message]
Squash last N commits (default: 2) with optional new commit message
.TP
.B amend
Amend the previous commit with new changes

