.SH ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
.TP
.B GITCOMMIT_NO_CONFIRM
Skip confirmation prompts (default: true)
.TP
.B GITCOMMIT_PROJECT_DIR
Default project directory location
.TP
.B GITCOMMIT_CHANGELOG_FILE_NAME
Name of changelog file to update (default: CHANGELOG.md)
.TP
.B GITCOMMIT_ROOT_DIR
Current Git repository root directory
.TP
.B GITCOMMIT_DEFAULT_AI_COMMAND
Preferred AI tool for commit message generation (ollama, claude, codex, copilot, llama-cli, llamafile, gpt4all-cli, lms)
.TP
.B GITCOMMIT_DEFAULT_AI_ARGS
Custom arguments for the AI command (e.g., "run mistral" for ollama, "-p --model opus" for claude)
.TP
.B GITCOMMIT_LOG_SHOW_EXCLUDE
Pipe-separated regex patterns to exclude from "log show" command (default: "Version Bump:"). Example: "Version Bump:|Merge|fixup"
.TP
.B GITCOMMIT_SIGNING_KEY
GPG key id used for signing when neither the repo-local nor the global \fBuser.signingkey\fR is set. See \fBGPG SIGNING\fR below
.TP
.B GITCOMMIT_GPG_CACHE_TTL
Target value (in seconds) for gpg-agent's \fBdefault-cache-ttl\fR, applied when \fBgitcommit --config\fR runs. Default \fB28800\fR (8 hours). Set to \fB0\fR/\fBno\fR/\fBoff\fR/\fBskip\fR/\fBfalse\fR/\fBdisabled\fR to leave \fI~/.gnupg/gpg-agent.conf\fR alone
.TP
.B GITCOMMIT_GPG_PASSPHRASE
GPG passphrase for non-interactive contexts (CI/CD, AI agents). Loaded into gpg-agent at script startup. See \fBNON-INTERACTIVE PASSPHRASE\fR below
.TP
.B GITCOMMIT_GPG_PASSPHRASE_FILE
Path to a file containing the GPG passphrase (intended mode \fB0600\fR). Used when \fB$GITCOMMIT_GPG_PASSPHRASE\fR is unset. When this var itself is unset, \fBgitcommit\fR auto-picks the first valid candidate from \fI/var/run/secrets/gpg/pass\fR (k8s/CI mount) then \fI~/.gnupg/commit_pass.txt\fR (per-user stash). Files must contain at least one non-blank line of actual text; empty or whitespace-only files are silently skipped
.TP
.B GITCOMMIT_GPG_PASSPHRASE_STDIN
Set to \fB1\fR/\fBtrue\fR to read the passphrase from stdin at script startup. Used as the third fallback after env var and file
.TP
.B GITCOMMIT_GPG_KEYGRIP
Manual override for the GPG keygrip used by \fBgpg-preset-passphrase\fR. Normally auto-detected via \fBgpg --with-keygrip\fR; override only if auto-detection fails

.SH GPG SIGNING
Every commit and version-bump made by \fBgitcommit\fR is signed. The signing key is resolved in this order:
.IP \(bu 2
Repo-local \fBgit config user.signingkey\fR (per-repo override always wins)
.IP \(bu 2
\fB$GITCOMMIT_SIGNING_KEY\fR env var (or \fBsettings.conf\fR entry)
.IP \(bu 2
Global \fBgit config --global user.signingkey\fR
.IP \(bu 2
If none of the above are set, \fBgitcommit\fR falls back to bare \fB-S\fR and lets gpg pick its default key
.PP
The same precedence applies to release tags created by \fBgitcommit release\fR; tags use \fB-s -u <keyid>\fR rather than \fB-S<keyid>\fR.
.SS gpg-agent passphrase caching
Running \fBgitcommit --config\fR (only the explicit invocation \(em not the silent auto-init that fires when \fBsettings.conf\fR is absent) updates \fI~/.gnupg/gpg-agent.conf\fR so the GPG passphrase is cached between commits. The update is idempotent and safe to re-run:
.IP \(bu 2
If \fBdefault-cache-ttl\fR or \fBmax-cache-ttl\fR is missing, it is appended
.IP \(bu 2
If present but lower than the target, it is replaced in-place; existing comments and unrelated directives (e.g. \fBpinentry-program\fR) are preserved
.IP \(bu 2
If already at or above the target, the file is left untouched
.PP
The target is \fB$GITCOMMIT_GPG_CACHE_TTL\fR (default \fB28800\fR seconds = 8 hours); \fBmax-cache-ttl\fR is set to \fB86400\fR or the same value as \fBdefault-cache-ttl\fR if larger. After modification \fBgpg-connect-agent reloadagent /bye\fR is called automatically. Set the env var to \fB0\fR/\fBno\fR/\fBoff\fR/\fBskip\fR to disable this behavior.
.PP
\fBgitcommit --config\fR also appends \fBallow-preset-passphrase\fR and \fBallow-loopback-pinentry\fR to \fI~/.gnupg/gpg-agent.conf\fR (idempotently). Both directives are required by the non-interactive paths described in the next section; they have no effect on interactive use.
.SS Non-interactive passphrase
For CI/CD pipelines, AI agents, and other non-interactive contexts that cannot answer a passphrase prompt, \fBgitcommit\fR can preload the passphrase into \fBgpg-agent\fR at script startup. The passphrase is sourced in this order:
.IP 1. 4
\fB$GITCOMMIT_GPG_PASSPHRASE\fR \(em literal env var (typical for CI runners)
.IP 2. 4
\fB$GITCOMMIT_GPG_PASSPHRASE_FILE\fR \(em explicit file path
.IP 3. 4
Auto-detected default file: \fI/var/run/secrets/gpg/pass\fR (k8s/CI secret mount) if present, else \fI~/.gnupg/commit_pass.txt\fR
.IP 4. 4
\fBstdin\fR, if \fB$GITCOMMIT_GPG_PASSPHRASE_STDIN\fR is set to \fB1\fR or \fBtrue\fR
.PP
Files in steps 2 and 3 must contain at least one non-blank line of actual text. Empty files, whitespace-only files, and missing files are silently skipped \(em the resolver simply continues to the next source. Only the first non-blank line of the chosen file is used as the passphrase, so a trailing newline left by an editor will not be appended to the passphrase.
.PP
Once a passphrase is resolved, \fBgitcommit\fR tries two injection paths in order:
.IP \(bu 2
\fBPreset (preferred)\fR \(em invoke \fBgpg-preset-passphrase --preset <keygrip>\fR with the passphrase on stdin. The keygrip is resolved via \fBgpg --with-keygrip --with-colons --list-secret-keys <key>\fR, or taken from \fB$GITCOMMIT_GPG_KEYGRIP\fR if set. Requires \fBallow-preset-passphrase\fR in \fIgpg-agent.conf\fR. After preset, normal \fBgit commit -S<key>\fR works prompt-free until the agent's \fBdefault-cache-ttl\fR expires
.IP \(bu 2
\fBLoopback fallback\fR \(em used when \fBgpg-preset-passphrase\fR isn't installed or the keygrip can't be resolved. \fBgitcommit\fR writes the passphrase to a \fB0600\fR tempfile under \fI$GITCOMMIT_TEMP_DIR\fR and a tiny wrapper that invokes \fBgpg --batch --pinentry-mode loopback --passphrase-file <tempfile>\fR. The wrapper is exposed to git as \fBgpg.program\fR via \fBGIT_CONFIG_KEY_*\fR / \fBGIT_CONFIG_VALUE_*\fR env vars so every \fBgit\fR invocation in this script picks it up. Requires \fBallow-loopback-pinentry\fR in \fIgpg-agent.conf\fR. Cleanup happens via the \fBEXIT\fR trap
.PP
The init runs exactly once per script invocation, immediately after \fIsettings.conf\fR is sourced and the temp directory is created. If no passphrase source is configured, init is a no-op and the original interactive behavior is preserved.

.SH FEATURES
.TP
.B Self-Contained
No external function dependencies - fully portable single-file script
.TP
.B Intelligent File Tracking
Automatically detects and categorizes changed files by type
.TP
.B Semantic Commits
Supports conventional commit patterns and semantic versioning
.TP
.B Changelog Integration
Automatically updates changelog files when present
.TP
.B Version Management
Automated version bumping and tagging
.TP
.B Emoji Support
Optional emoji-based commit messages
.TP
.B AI Integration
Generate commit messages using local AI (ollama, llama.cpp, llamafile, gpt4all, lmstudio) or cloud AI (claude, codex, copilot) with automatic fallback chain and output validation
.TP
.B Search Capability
Search through commit history efficiently
.TP
.B Multi-Repository
Manage commits across multiple repositories with --dir option
.TP
.B Message Persistence
Read commit messages from .git/COMMIT_MESS file
.TP
.B Git Signing
Full support for GPG commit signing

.SH WORKFLOW INTEGRATION
gitcommit integrates seamlessly with various Git workflows:
.TP
.B Feature Branch Workflow
Use 'gitcommit branch' to create feature branches
.TP
.B Conventional Commits
Supports semantic commit types (feat, fix, docs, etc.)
.TP
.B CI/CD Integration
Works with automated deployment pipelines
.TP
.B Changelog Generation
Automatically updates CHANGELOG.md files

.SH SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS
.TP
.B No External Dependencies
Self-contained script eliminates supply chain vulnerabilities
.TP
.B GPG Signing Support
Respects Git's commit signing configuration
.TP
.B Safe Force Push
Warns before force pushing to prevent data loss
.TP
.B Permission Handling
Proper file permissions for config and credential files

.SH REQUIREMENTS
.TP
.B Git
Git version control system must be installed
.TP
.B Bash
Bash shell version 4.0 or higher

.SH NOTES
gitcommit is a fully self-contained script with all functions inlined, making it highly portable and independent of external function libraries. It has been refactored to remove all external dependencies while maintaining full functionality.

The script supports the .git/COMMIT_MESS file pattern for integration with AI assistants and automated commit workflows.

